<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="awkward-adj">awkward <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'ɔːkwəd/    美 /'ɔːkwərd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>尴尬的；别扭的</strong></h4>
<p>embarrassing：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>an <strong>awkward silence</strong>
令人尴尬的沉默</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I felt awkward, so I smiled at him.
我感到很尴尬，冲他笑了笑。</p><footer>外研⑦ – 5</footer></div>

<h4 id="2-difficult">2.★ <strong>使用不便的；难以应付的(difficult)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>an awkward machine
不好用的机器</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>ask an awkward question
问一个难以回答的问题</p></div>

<h4 id="3-inconvenient">3.★ <strong>不方便的 (inconvenient)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Please arrange the next meeting at a less awkward time. 
请把下次会议时间安排得方便些。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>awkwardly /'ɔːkwədli/ adv   </p></div>